A 20-year-old girl identified as Ebunoluwa Osatuyi been killed by unknown persons in Ondo State. The deceased was gruesomely murdered in her father’s house at the Okuta Elerinla Akure. Ebunoluwa who was a university seeker was killed during the weekend shortly after she returned from a coaching centre where had gone for tutorials ahead of the forthcoming Unified Tertiary Matriculation Examination, UTME. Allow Peace To Reign In Bauchi, Mohammed Tells Opposition… APC Drifting, Exposing Damaged Profile – Lukman Warns… The deceased was said to have been killed after she met some burglars in her father’s house who had gained access to the house through the windows. It was gathered that the lifeless body of Ebunoluwa was discovered in a pool of blood by her mother, Bosede Osatuyi, after returning home in the evening. The distraught mother said, “My husband and I entered the sitting room and found our daughter with her two hands tied with rope on the floor. She was bleeding profusely and we saw bloodstain on the chair including a rope hung on the fan. “We quickly rushed her to the hospital immediately where she was confirmed dead before we went to the police station to report.” The State Police Public Relations Officer in the state, PPRO, FunmilayoOdunlami who confirmed the report disclosed that investigation had commenced following the incident. POLL The PPRO said, “The parents are not suspecting anybody but we have commenced investigation into the matter.”